Crispin Bevington, 41, known as Chris, was a director of global partnerships at the music-streaming service Spotify, which has an office in central Stockholm."We are all devastated by the untimely and tragic death of our talented, compassionate and caring son Chris," his father, John Bevington, said. "[He was ] a wonderful husband, son, father, brother and close friend to many."Bevington was born in South Africa. He spent some of his childhood in Durban before the family moved to the UK.Spotify's office is just a short walk away from Queen's Street, the shopping district where a suspected Islamic extremist ploughed through a crowd of people on Friday afternoon.Daniel Ek, CEO and founder of Spotify, said he was "devastated" by the news.Swedish police have disclosed that the suspect, named as Rakhmat Akilov, 39, from Uzbekistan, was a failed asylum seeker.He is in police custody and was expected to appear in court yesterday . - edited by The Times